I love writing about what is wonderful in Northern Ontario; arts, cuisine, music, theatre, culture, shopping, canoeing, kayaking and the people who create so much elegance and beauty in this region.

Manhattan Manitoulin is my second novel, published by Scrivner Press out of Sudbury and in it's second printing. I am thrilled about this!

My next novel is titled, The Boat That Brings You Home, a love and murder mystery which takes place upon the Caribbean Sea. It begins in the North Channel by Little Current and sails southward to the luscious Caribbean Islands.

about:
Andrew Logan has been an integral part of worship for more than 20 years. Passionately, he escorts others into the Presence of God. Andrew maintains that worship invites God to meet with us to bring lasting life transformation that won't come any other way.

Andrew developed a personal relationship with Jesus Christ during a time of intense struggle in his personal life. Having a strong passion for music, he served the Lord in music ministries in several churches. A few years later, the founder of Life Bible Ministries International, Dr. Harold Hagen ordained Andrew and asked him to lead worship there.

After a rewarding career of more than twenty years in Information Technology, he transitioned into full-time Pastoral Ministry. Andrew now serves as senior pastor of All Nations Word and Worship Center.

name: Malachai Grove
about: I grew up working like a man on the farm & learned the basics of farming, carpentry& mechanics & excelled in mechanical & architectural drafting. Of course I did pretty well in the shop classes as well as the arts. I graduated top of my class from Sequoia Institute diesel training program after my discharge from the air force where I had achieved a journeyman level jet engine mechanic rating. I was always good at puzzle solving & if there was a lost item that could not be found they came to me. I ran my own second hand / marina & mechanic shop for years while doing my artwork creations. I sold many & gave away most. Because of my abusive upbringing I have a special passion to help abused & underpriveledged children Everywhere. When I was in 1st grade I was the only one in the class already in the second grade reader. So you can see because of my affinity for learning and my natural talents centering around creativity & construction I think I have finally found a way to help. Abraham Lincoln was my inspiration. I have studied natural healing techniques from many different cultures throughout history. Now I have gotten my health back & am not taking any medications whatsoever. I know I can help others with what I have learned. The product of my passion enabled by my abilities has created a disaster proof earthship design With a huge biodome greenhouse in the center. The children will survive.

name: Ian O
about:
I'm coming at this as an opportunity to map out my life as a reader. Hopefully, once I am done, I will have a nice cross-section of books from different phases of my life and some detail to go with that.

I used to put a lot of stock in what I read as a marker of self-identity. That isn't so much the case anymore. It makes this process of listing all these books a sort of meditation. I am trying to be fairly objective in the list, in part to strengthen that distance between my person and my reading.
